  "local_port": 41642,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "PAN Card: I lost my Aadhaar card. How can I get a second copy?",
  "response": "If you have lost your Aadhaar card, you can get a duplicate copy through several methods. Here are the steps you can follow to get a second copy of your Aadhaar card:\n\n### Online Method:\n1. **Visit the UIDAI Website:**\n   - Go to the official website of the Unique Identification Authority of India (UIDAI) at [uidai.gov.in](https://uidai.gov.in).\n\n2. **Retrieve Aadhaar Number/Enrolment ID:**\n   - If you do not remember your Aadhaar number or enrolment ID, visit the \u201cMy Aadhaar\u201d section, then click on the \u201cRetrieve Lost or Forgotten EID/UID\u201d link.\n   \n3. **Fill in Required Details:**\n   - Provide your full name, email address, or mobile number (as registered with Aadhaar), and the security code displayed on the page.\n   - Click on \u201cSend OTP\u201d or \u201cSend TOTP\u201d if using the mAadhaar app.\n\n4. **Verify OTP:**\n   - An OTP (One-Time Password) will be sent to your registered email ID or mobile number. Enter this OTP in the provided field and verify.\n\n5. **Download e-Aadhaar:**\n   - Once verified, you can proceed to download the e-Aadhaar by clicking on the \u201cDownload Aadhaar\u201d link.\n   - Enter your Aadhaar number/eID (Enrolment ID), name, pin-code, and the security code displayed.\n   - Click on \u201cGet OTP\u201d and enter the OTP sent to your registered mobile number.\n   - Your e-Aadhaar card will be downloaded in PDF format. You can open this file using the password, which is the first four letters of your name in capital letters followed by your year of birth.\n\n### Offline Method:\n1. **Visit an Aadhaar Enrolment/Update Center:**\n   - Locate the nearest Aadhaar enrolment/update center. You can find this on the UIDAI website.\n\n2. **Fill the Aadhaar Card Correction/Update Form:**\n   - Fill out the form for retrieving the Aadhaar card and submit the required documents for identity and address proof.\n\n3. **Biometric Verification:**\n   - Submit your biometric details for verification purposes.\n\n4. **Collect Aadhaar Card:**\n   - After submission and verification, you will receive a reprinted Aadhaar card at your registered address within a few days.\n\n### UIDAI Mobile App:\n1. **Download mAadhaar App:**\n   - Install the mAadhaar app available on Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n\n2. **Login/Register:**\n   - Register or log in using your Aadhaar number and OTP sent to your registered mobile number.\n\n3. **Download Aadhaar:**\n   - Use the app to download your e-Aadhaar and save it to your device.\n\nBy following these steps, you can easily get a duplicate copy of your Aadhaar card. Make sure your mobile number is registered with your Aadhaar to receive OTPs for verification.",
